
1/ Install docker ce

	https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/

2/ Build docker image

	sudo docker build -t dapp-java:latest -f Dockerfile.java .
	sudo docker build -t dapp-exec:latest -f Dockerfile.exec .

3/ Run cc container

	sudo docker run -it --memory=10m --cpus="0.01" -v $PDX_HOME/dapps:/dapps/ dapp-java HelloWorld.jar
	sudo docker run -it --memory=10m --cpus="0.01" -v $PDX_HOME/dapps:/dapps/ dapp-exec test 

	Here, the storage, memory and cpu limits are from chaincode deployment requirements. 
	The cost of deploying and invoking a dapp proportionately correlates to the 
	memory, cpu, disk and network requirements.

4) Start/stop dapp-* container

	Via open-sourced, security-hardened setuid'd sandboxer 
	 
